<item>
            <title>[HBASE-15820] Re-using byte[] from Bytes can save some objects creations</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-15820</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-15233&quot; title=&quot;Bytes.toBytes() methods should allow arrays to be re-used &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-15233&quot;&gt;HBASE-15233&lt;/a&gt; will allow byte arrays re-usage for Bytes.toBytes() methods. CellCodec can benefit from that in many places.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Patch will follow as soon as there is one in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-15233&quot; title=&quot;Bytes.toBytes() methods should allow arrays to be re-used &quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-15233&quot;&gt;HBASE-15233&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
