                            <comment id="15281522" author="anoop.hbase" created="Thu, 12 May 2016 13:37:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We don&apos;t really use CellCodec.  And one more thing to consider is that reusing the byte[] keep its ref active for longer time and possibly not allow to die in young gen. It depends on the usage. Still some thing to consider.. For very small sized byte[] not that much relevant may be. But for large sized byte[] some thing to really consider.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15281525" author="jmspaggi" created="Thu, 12 May 2016 13:44:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, I checked for the references. Arrays are copied in the methods that are called. So it&apos;s fine. And it&apos;s all small arrays here, so it should be fine. Just sad that  it&apos;s not used that much. There is also optimization on filters, etc. But again, small usage.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
